{{Han compound|𠦝|月|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}}

The left side ({{lang|zh|𠦝}}) is a pictograph of the sunrise as seen through some trees. The right-side {{lang|zh|月}} is actually a graphical corruption of {{zh-l|*川|river}}.

===Etymology===
“Morning” > “perform the morning ceremony” > “to go/come to court; to have an audience”. Derivative: {{och-l|潮|morning tide}}.

Perhaps related to {{cog|th|เพรา||morning}} ({{zh-ref|Manomaivibool, 1975}}).

